* Hot Plug

You can plug in or remove the device while the system is running.

The system detects it without rebooting.

Example: USB drive, mouse, keyboard, HDMI cable.

* Cold Plug

The device must be plugged in before the system starts.

You usually need to reboot the computer to use the device.

Example: Older PCI cards, some internal components like RAM or hard drives (without hot-swap support).
